title.narrative: Liberia Road Asset Management Project - LIBRAMP

description.narrative: The objective of the project is to support the Recipient's efforts to reduce transport costs along the road corridor from Monroviato the Guinea border and to maintain the road in good condition over a 10-year period.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Article V, Section 5.01 | Description :The Co-financing Agreement has been executed and delivered and allconditions precedent to its effectiveness or to the right of theRecipient to make withdrawals under it have been fulfilled. | DueDate :13-Oct-2011
Finance Agreement :Sch. 2, Sec. I.D.4 | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than December 31, 2011, recruit a safeguardsspecialist | Due Date :31-Dec-2011
Finance Agreement :Sch. 2, Sec. III.E. | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than December 31, 2011, recruit twoprocurement specialists. | Due Date :31-Dec-2011

Finance Agreement :Sch.2, Section II.B.4 | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than four months after the Effective Date,recruit an independent and qualified external auditor. | Due Date :12-Feb-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I B 1 (a) | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than March 1st of each calendaryear, prepare and furnish to the Association, a plan of activities covering all activities proposed to be carried out in thefollowing calendar year, together with a budget, including amounts of Counterpart Funding required for the purpose. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, A | Description :The Recipient shall not later than September 30, 2017 or any other dateagreed with the Association update the Program in a manner satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :30-Sep-2017
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, B 1 | Description :Payment of the annual GOL counterpart funds into the Project Account| Frequency :Yearly
